{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014tD9uRWbbQGUW4dmmdTS96","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the problem:\n\n- Columns B-F are unit1-unit5 with values for rows 2-18\n- Column I has residuals\n- Row 20 has min constraints, row 21 has max constraints\n- For positive residuals: ADD to units from unit1 to unit5 (left to right)\n- For negative residuals: SUBTRACT from units from unit5 to unit1 (right to left)\n- Don't change cells that are zero\n- At the end, set column I values to 0\n\nSo for each row:\n- If residual is positive, we need to distribute the residual by adding to unit1 first (up to its max), then unit2, etc.\n\n\n- If residual is negative, we need to absorb the deficit by subtracting from unit5 first (down to its min), then unit4, etc.\n\nNow I'll write the code to implement this logic.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1581,"cache_read_input_tokens":13677,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1581},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"00003d7b-e9c7-4806-a6b2-129e192396b7","uuid":"133a2c80-927e-4669-9ca3-fab0f1d2526b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014tD9uRWbbQGUW4dmmdTS96","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KKeTTL3aDoF94Ar2HdbJ3p","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport openpyxl\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook('input.xlsx')\nws = wb['Sheet1']\n\n# Read min/max constraints for units 1-5 (columns B-F)\nmins = [ws.cell(20, c).value for c in range(2, 7)]  # B20:F20\nmaxs = [ws.cell(21, c).value for c in range(2, 7)]  # B21:F21\n\nprint(f\"Mins: {mins}\")\nprint(f\"Maxs: {maxs}\")\n\nfor row in range(2, 19):  # rows 2-18\n    residual = ws.cell(row, 9).value  # column I\n    if residual is None or residual == 0:\n        continue\n    \n    units = [ws.cell(row, c).value for c in range(2, 7)]\n    print(f\"\\nRow {row}: units={units}, residual={residual}\")\n    \n    remaining = residual\n    \n    if residual > 0:\n        # Add from unit1 to unit5 (left to right)\n        for i in range(5):\n            if units[i] is None or units[i] == 0:\n                continue\n            can_add = maxs[i] - units[i]\n            add = min(remaining, can_add)\n            if add > 0:\n                units[i] += add\n                remaining -= add\n            if remaining == 0:\n                break\n    else:  # residual < 0\n        # Subtract from unit5 to unit1 (right to left)\n        deficit = -remaining  # positive amount to subtract\n        for i in range(4, -1, -1):\n            if units[i] is None or units[i] == 0:\n                continue\n            can_sub = units[i] - mins[i]\n            sub = min(deficit, can_sub)\n            if sub > 0:\n                units[i] -= sub\n                deficit -= sub\n            if deficit == 0:\n                break\n        remaining = -deficit\n    \n    # Write back units\n    for i in range(5):\n        ws.cell(row, 2 + i).value = units[i]\n    \n    print(f\"  -> units={units}, remaining={remaining}\")\n\n# Set column I to 0 for data rows\nfor row in range(2, 19):\n    ws.cell(row, 9).value = 0\n\nwb.save('output.xlsx')\nprint(\"\\nDone!\")\nEOF\n","description":"Process residuals and save output.xlsx"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1581,"cache_read_input_tokens":13677,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1581},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"00003d7b-e9c7-4806-a6b2-129e192396b7","uuid":"ec3681b4-01a6-4a66-8bf7-7deef0756f4b"}
